Das IRI f&uuml;r Lebenswissenschaften l&auml;dt ein zum 
&lt;strong&gt;Antrittssymposium f&uuml;r Prof. Dr. Nils Bl&uuml;thgen &amp; Dr. Benedikt Beckmann&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Dienstag, den 10. Juni 2014, 15:00-17:30 Uhr&lt;br /&gt;Festsaal Luisenstr. 56, Berlin-Mitte&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;Gastvortrag Prof. Chris Sander&amp;nbsp; Ph.D. (Memorial Sloan Kettering Cancer Center, New York)&lt;br /&gt;&ldquo;Using statistical physics in evolutionary biology and network pharmacology&rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;Antrittsvorlesung Dr. Benedikt Beckmann (IRI &ndash; Nachwuchsgruppenleiter Molekulare Infektionsbiologie)&lt;br /&gt;&quot;Searching for cross-species RNA-protein interactions during infection&quot;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;Antrittsvorlesung Prof. Dr. Nils Bl&uuml;thgen (IRI &ndash; Charit&eacute; Professor f&uuml;r Mathematische Modellierung in der Medizin)&lt;br /&gt;&ldquo;Dissecting complex regulatory networks with computational modeling: From perturbation data to combinatorial therapies&rdquo;
&lt;br /&gt;--------------------------------------
&lt;strong&gt;Invitation&lt;/strong&gt;
In an inaugural symposium on &lt;strong&gt;June 10th, 2014 from 3 p.m. to 5:30 p.m. in the Festsaal of the Luisenstr. 56&lt;/strong&gt; the IRI for the Life Sciences introduces the first IRI professor together with the first independent junior research group leader at the IRI.
Guest speaker Prof. Chris Sander&amp;nbsp; Ph.D. (Memorial Sloan Kettering Cancer Center, New York)&lt;br /&gt;&ldquo;Using statistical physics in evolutionary biology and network pharmacology&rdquo;
Inaugural lecture Dr. Benedikt Beckmann (IRI &ndash; independent junior research group leader &ldquo;Molecular Infection Biology&ldquo;)&lt;br /&gt;&quot;Searching for cross-species RNA-protein interactions during infection&quot;
